  "prompt": "Which are some kickass CV/ resume you have ever seen?",
  "response": "While I can't browse the internet or view specific CVs or resumes, I can certainly describe some key elements that make a CV or resume \"kickass\" based on best practices and trends. Here are some standout features:\n\n1. **Clean and Professional Layout**: A well-structured layout with clear sections, consistent fonts, and adequate white space enhances readability. Use of bullet points and headers can help guide the reader\u2019s eye.\n\n2. **Personal Branding**: Incorporating personal branding elements, such as a unique but professional color scheme, logo, or tagline, can make a resume memorable.\n\n3. **Tailored Content**: A standout resume is customized for the specific job application. It highlights relevant experience and skills that match the job description.\n\n4. **Quantifiable Achievements**: Instead of simply listing responsibilities, successful resumes feature quantifiable achievements (e.g., \"Increased sales by 30% in six months\" or \"Managed a team of 10\").\n\n5. **Strong Summary Statement**: A compelling summary or objective statement at the top can quickly communicate who you are and what you bring to the table.\n\n6. **Skills Section**: A dedicated skills section that highlights both hard and soft skills relevant to the position can capture the reader\u2019s attention.\n\n7. **Use of Action Verbs**: Starting bullet points with strong action verbs (e.g., \"developed,\" \"led,\" \"implemented\") conveys proactivity and impact.\n\n8. **Incorporation of Keywords**: Utilizing keywords from the job description can help a resume get past applicant tracking systems (ATS) and into the hands of a recruiter.\n\n9. **Visual Elements**: For creative roles, including visual elements like infographics or charts can showcase creativity and make the document visually appealing.\n\n10. **Projects and Portfolios**: Including links to projects, publications, or a portfolio website can provide tangible evidence of skills and accomplishments.\n\n11. **Certifications and Ongoing Education**: Highlighting relevant certifications or ongoing education shows commitment to professional development.\n\n12. **Testimonials or Endorsements**: Including short testimonials or quotes from previous employers can add credibility and a personal touch.\n\nFor inspiration, you might look at examples from platforms like Canva, Behance, or LinkedIn, where users share innovative and stylish resumes.",
